goals.question: What is the correlation between deaths and year?

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='Year')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['Year'], data['Deaths'], color='blue', linewidth=2)
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Deaths')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of deaths over the years?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='Deaths', ascending=False)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax.bar(data['Entity'], data['Deaths'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Entity')
    ax.set_ylabel('Deaths')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of deaths across different entities?')
    ax.spines['top'].set_visible(False)
    ax.spines['right'].set_visible(False)
    ax.tick_params(axis='x', rotation=90)
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Year'].dt.year
    avg_deaths = data['Deaths'].mean()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.plot(data['Year'], data['Deaths'], label='Deaths')
    ax.axhline(avg_deaths, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Deaths: {avg_deaths:.2f}')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Deaths')
    ax.set_title('What is the average number of deaths per year?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from typing import List

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='Year')
    data['Deaths_pct_change'] = data['Deaths'].pct_change() * 100
    plt.plot(data['Year'], data['Deaths_pct_change'], color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=data['Deaths_pct_change'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Median')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Percentage Change in Deaths')
    plt.title('What is the percentage change in deaths between consecutive years?')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['Year'], data['Deaths'], color='blue')
    ax.axhline(y=data['Deaths'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean Deaths')
    ax.legend(loc='best')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Deaths')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between deaths and year?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
